  "texts": [
    "We separate the proof of this theorem into two parts, one for the freeness of the group A(L)/A(L) tor and the other for the infiniteness of the rank of the group A(L).",
    "First, we show the former part.",
    "Let σ ∈ G e K satisfy the following: for any finite extension M of K(σ), only finitely many roots of unity belong to M and the group B(M) tor is finite for any abelian variety B over M.",
    "Since e ≥ 2, almost all σ ∈ G e K satisfy this condition by Theorems 3.1 (2-ii) and 3.2 (1).",
    "Let L be a finite extension of K[σ] and M = L • K(σ)."
  ],
